01/09/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Parliament's two chambers passed a series of bills related to Romania's EU membership bid at an extraordinary session Tuesday (31 August).
The package included legislation concerning economic reforms, insurance and the civil service, as well as the freezing of state-run enterprises' debts.
Lawmakers also adopted measures on personal data protection and on simplifying procedures to establish businesses, in line with EU practices.
(Rompres - 01/09/04;
Nine o'clock - 31/08/04)
